          "id": 5,
          "question": "<p><a name=\"335155\"></a><div itemprop=\"text\"><p>A binary \\( 3 \\)-bit down counter&nbsp;uses \\( J \\)-\\( K \\) flip-flops, \\( FF_{i} \\) with inputs \\( J_{i} \\),&nbsp;\\( K_{i} \\) and outputs \\( Q_{i} \\), \\( i \\) = \\( 0, 1, 2 \\) respectively. The minimized expression for the input from following&nbsp;is :</p>\n\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:upper-roman\" type=\"I\">\n\t<li>\\( J_{0} = K_{0} = 0 \\)</li>\n\t<li>\\( J_{0} = K_{0} = 1 \\)</li>\n\t<li>\\( J_{1} = K_{1} = Q_{0} \\)</li>\n\t<li>\\( J_{1} = K_{1} = \\overline{Q}_{0} \\)</li>\n\t<li>\\( J_{2} = K_{2} =Q_{1}&nbsp;Q_{0} \\)</li>\n\t<li>\\( J_{2} = K_{2} =\\overline{Q}_{1} \\overline{Q}_{0} \\)</li>\n</ol>\n\n</div><br><br><b>UGC NET CSE | January 2017 | Part 2 | Question: 8</b></p>",
          "type": "single",
